    },
    {
      "id": "hPiGtuM7pwOgQEQ_49YbW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -8467.059637020584,
      "y": 5713.106128476125,
      "width": 1709.6396773631564,
      "height": 105,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2118296141,
      "version": 118,
      "versionNonce": 1552250477,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1778326204608,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Producer at 10 k msg/s, consumer artificially slowed to ~1.9 k msg/s capacity. Lag grows unbounded := 309 thousand\nmessages in 40 seconds. End-to-end p99 reaches 31 seconds. Delivery ratio 26.6%.\n ====> unbounded-queue failure mode: ρ = λ/μ = 5.16 > 1, Little's Law guarantees the queue grows forever.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Producer at 10 k msg/s, consumer artificially slowed to ~1.9 k msg/s capacity. Lag grows unbounded := 309 thousand messages in 40 seconds. End-to-end p99 reaches 31 seconds. Delivery ratio 26.6%.\n ====> unbounded-queue failure mode: ρ = λ/μ = 5.16 > 1, Little's Law guarantees the queue grows forever.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "vhZbHplPuHj0At3Bs-LZL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -8486.305125744915,
      "y": 6016.205645833307,
      "width": 1840.0209083387704,
      "height": 245,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bER",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 109712931,
      "version": 121,
      "versionNonce": 1899496163,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1778326257046,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Same setup, but at t=30s we atomically swap the consumer delay to zero.\n\nLag peaks at 195 k, then drains at a measurable 3 726 msg/s. The end-to-end CDF becomes bimodal: messages produced before the\nslow phase or after recovery clear in <10 ms; messages produced during the slow phase pile up at 5–20 seconds because they had to\nwait their turn behind the backlog. \n\n=========> if I know my outage built up X messages, I'll catch up in X / 3726 seconds.'",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Same setup, but at t=30s we atomically swap the consumer delay to zero.\n\nLag peaks at 195 k, then drains at a measurable 3 726 msg/s. The end-to-end CDF becomes bimodal: messages produced before the slow phase or after recovery clear in <10 ms; messages produced during the slow phase pile up at 5–20 seconds because they had to wait their turn behind the backlog. \n\n=========> if I know my outage built up X messages, I'll catch up in X / 3726 seconds.'",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "LGHDmSVSvN6FJEvf9-UXk",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -8517.162669289297,
      "y": 6303.551907394865,
      "width": 1593.5396766306026,
      "height": 315,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bES",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 909787533,
      "version": 159,
      "versionNonce": 2029371267,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1778326433825,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": " We added a producer that alternates between 5 k baseline and 15 k / 30 k bursts on a 25% duty cycle. \n\nThe interesting result is the absorption boundary: light burst (15 k) and heavy burst (30 k with no consumer delay)\nboth absorb cleanly because the off-window has enough drain capacity.\n\n Overload (30 k burst with an 800 µs consumer delay) cannot, because the time-averaged demand exceeds the\nconsumer's sustained capacity. The boundary isn't the burst peak \n\nit's time-averaged demand vs sustained service rate. Constant-rate benchmarks miss this entirely.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": " We added a producer that alternates between 5 k baseline and 15 k / 30 k bursts on a 25% duty cycle. \n\nThe interesting result is the absorption boundary: light burst (15 k) and heavy burst (30 k with no consumer delay) both absorb cleanly because the off-window has enough drain capacity.\n\n Overload (30 k burst with an 800 µs consumer delay) cannot, because the time-averaged demand exceeds the consumer's sustained capacity. The boundary isn't the burst peak \n\nit's time-averaged demand vs sustained service rate. Constant-rate benchmarks miss this entirely.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8fjBtrB291_jqGqGXGpe0",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -8568.577341635064,
      "y": 6700.560705439064,
      "width": 2033.9211498628429,
      "height": 265.0245669310999,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bET",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1635252931,
      "version": 156,
      "versionNonce": 1265326883,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1778326468553,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now we go back to the slow-consumer scenario and turn on the credit-based backpressure controller. Same producer,\nsame consumer delay, same 40 seconds. Peak lag drops from 309 k to 12 k, a 96% reduction. End-to-end p99 drops\nfrom 31 seconds to 3.8 seconds, 88% reduction. Delivery ratio goes from 26.6% to 100%. The cost is producer\nthroughput: it self-throttles from 9.7 k to 1.9 k msg/s, which is exactly the consumer's sustained capacity. The\n'lost' producer rate was already lost in the 26.6% delivery hole, backpressure trades dropped throughput for\nguaranteed responsiveness.",
      "fontSize": 35.33660892414665,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now we go back to the slow-consumer scenario and turn on the credit-based backpressure controller. Same producer, same consumer delay, same 40 seconds. Peak lag drops from 309 k to 12 k, a 96% reduction. End-to-end p99 drops from 31 seconds to 3.8 seconds, 88% reduction. Delivery ratio goes from 26.6% to 100%. The cost is producer throughput: it self-throttles from 9.7 k to 1.9 k msg/s, which is exactly the consumer's sustained capacity. The 'lost' producer rate was already lost in the 26.6% delivery hole, backpressure trades dropped throughput for guaranteed responsiveness.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "SVhtpRzttsttIkaBhS1l4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -5682.134989062773,
      "y": -2857.0387319818815,
      "width": 992.6276245117188,
      "height": 35,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEU",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 451964429,
      "version": 109,
      "versionNonce": 1829508525,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1778328472818,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "shouldn've measured maximum consumer consumption rate! didn't do that.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "shouldn've measured maximum consumer consumption rate! didn't do that.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
